<br>
All analogies are weak because the fail to cover a topic completely.  They are mainly useful for getting a point across from a view people are failing to grasp (from your side).  They can not tell everything, only a small part of your arguement.<br>
<br>
A nation can fill all of the rolls you mentioned.  This is were perspective comes in.  From my perspective, the US is not a superhero by a long shot.  I'm not that nieve.  You could definately say we are both vigilante and cop though.  We are doing this mostly for ourselves and partial for the rest of the world.<br>
